CLYDE STEAMSHIP COMPANY, Appellant, v. NEW YORK TRAP ROCK CORPORATION, Appellee. No. 126. Circuit Count of Appeals, Second Circuit. Jan. 20, 1930. Burlingham, Veeder, Fearey, Clark & Hupper, of New York City (Chauncey I. Clark and Stanley R. Wright, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Frederick W. Park, of New York City, for respondent.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
